560
00:35:50,920 --> 00:35:53,200
So, how long do you keep it up?

561
00:35:55,520 --> 00:35:57,080
How long?

562
00:35:57,160 --> 00:36:00,440
Well, if time passes
and nothing significant materializes,

563
00:36:00,520 --> 00:36:05,040
how long do you keep on going
before you decide that?

564
00:36:05,120 --> 00:36:07,800
To try something else?

565
00:36:08,120 --> 00:36:10,520
I hardly think Nola's
reached that point, Mother.

566
00:36:10,600 --> 00:36:11,600
I'm not saying that.

567
00:36:11,680 --> 00:36:14,360
All I'm saying is
you give acting a try for a time,

568
00:36:14,440 --> 00:36:18,160
and if you keep being disappointed
you have to ask yourself the question,

569
00:36:18,200 --> 00:36:22,360
"Is this really what I want in my life?
Is this what I want?"

570
00:36:22,400 --> 00:36:24,680
Well, I do ask myself that.

571
00:36:24,760 --> 00:36:26,880
See? It's only logical, Tom.

572
00:36:26,960 --> 00:36:29,240
Especially for a woman.

573
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:32,160
It's a particularly
cruel business for a woman,

574
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:34,960
and as you get older and time passes,

575
00:36:35,040 --> 00:36:37,280
if nothing happens
it gets harder and harder.

576
00:36:38,040 --> 00:36:40,880
Eleanor,
Nola isn't exactly over the hill.

577
00:36:41,840 --> 00:36:44,520
I'm not saying now.

578
00:36:44,600 --> 00:36:48,560
But I'm a great one
for facing up to realities.

579
00:36:48,720 --> 00:36:51,640
Your take on these realities
is your own opinion and nothing else.

580
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:54,200
Frankly, not everybody else
is interested in hearing about it.

581
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:56,440
Tom, don't raise your voice
to your mother, please.

582
00:36:56,520 --> 00:36:58,560
I'm not raising my voice.
And I'm sorry, Papa,

583
00:36:58,640 --> 00:37:02,560
