01:03:08,960 --> 01:03:10,080
- Bye. See you.
- Thanks.

972
01:03:10,160 --> 01:03:11,120
Nuts.

973
01:03:12,440 --> 01:03:13,840
Good afternoon, Ingrid.

974
01:03:14,600 --> 01:03:16,760
Samantha, what do we have
for this afternoon?

975
01:03:16,840 --> 01:03:19,040
Just the Sarazin people at two.

976
01:03:19,120 --> 01:03:20,240
- Can we push it an hour?
- Yeah.

977
01:03:20,320 --> 01:03:23,560
I should be back in time, but if I'm
not, please make them comfortable.

978
01:03:27,640 --> 01:03:29,280
Chris. Where are you off to?

979
01:03:29,360 --> 01:03:31,440
I'm sorry, Rod,
I've got an appointment.

980
01:03:31,480 --> 01:03:33,680
We have Sarazin
and company this afternoon.

981
01:03:33,760 --> 01:03:36,680
I should be back in time but if I'm not,
please start without me.

982
01:03:36,800 --> 01:03:40,640
- Really?
- It's OK. It's important, trust me.

983
01:03:41,640 --> 01:03:43,480
It's ridiculous to go back to my place.

984
01:03:43,560 --> 01:03:45,400
Once we get there,
you'll have less than an hour.

985
01:03:45,480 --> 01:03:47,960
Look, it's not that I'm
miserable with Chloe, it's just...

986
01:03:48,000 --> 01:03:49,520
I don't wanna talk about Chloe anymore!

987
01:03:49,600 --> 01:03:51,720
Listen, it's just I'm bored!
I mean, she's very nice, but...

988
01:03:51,800 --> 01:03:53,680
- Chris!
- Are you in a bad mood?

989
01:03:53,760 --> 01:03:56,160
Yes, I am in a bad mood.
I just blew another audition.

990
01:03:56,240 --> 01:03:58,600
I'm so sick of this acting thing,
it's just not working out.

991
01:03:58,640 --> 01:03:59,720
It's a hard field.

992
01:03:59,800 --> 01:04:02,280
- You have to keep plugging at it.
- I'm sick of plugging.

993
01:04:02,360 --> 01:04:05,200
Tom's mother was right.
Itjust gets to a point, you know?

994
01:04:05,280 --> 01:04:07,040
Or should I say your mother-in-law?

995
01:04:07,080 --> 01:04:10,080
Hey, look.
Let's not go into one of those, OK?

996
01:04:11,280 --> 01:04:15,200
I don't know what I'm doing with you.
You're never gonna leave Chloe.

997
01:04:16,920 --> 01:04:18,920
Maybe I will.

998
01:04:21,080 --> 01:04:23,400
Don't say that unless you mean it.

999
01:04:24,920 --> 01:04:27,520
Chloe's just so desperate
to get pregnant.

1000
01:04:28,280 --> 01:04:30,640
I mean, it's... mechanical.

1001
01:04:34,840 --> 01:04:37,040
I don't know what I'd do
if I couldn't see you.

1002
01:04:38,960 --> 01:04:41,360
Really. I mean it.

1003
01:04:44,200 --> 01:04:46,880
- Merry bloody Christmas.
- Lovely.

1004
01:04:46,920 --> 01:04:48,640
How many cigarettes
are you gonna smoke today?

1005
01:04:48,720 --> 01:04:50,920
- A million, at least.
- Please don't start smoking.

1006
01:04:50,960 --> 01:04:52,840
- Well, it is Christmas.
- It's such a pity.

1007
01:04:52,920 --> 01:04:54,080
- Come on, just a little one.
- It's gonna...

1008
01:04:54,160 --> 01:04:56,600
You think you're going
to be living forever, you're not.

1009
01:04:56,800 --> 01:04:58,320
Hi.

1010
01:04:58,400 --> 01:05:00,720
I wanted to wish you a merry Christmas.

1011
01:05:01,880 --> 01:05:04,320
I've been thinking about you.

1012
01:05:06,640 --> 01:05:10,040
I may be able to get away tomorrow,
for an hour or so.

1013
01:05:11,520 --> 01:05:13,960
OK. See you then.

1014
01:05:14,040 --> 01:05:15,600
Bye-bye.

1015
01:05:16,280 --> 01:05:18,160
There you are, Chris.

1016
01:05:18,240 --> 01:05:21,600
Chloe tells me you've sustained
some personal loss in the market

1017
01:05:21,680 --> 01:05:23,440
over the past few months.

1018
01:05:23,520 --> 01:05:26,440
Well, I guess I've been a little bit
careless, not concentrating.

1019
01:05:26,520 --> 01:05:28,320
And, of course,
I thought I made good decisions, but...

1020
01:05:28,400 --> 01:05:30,200
Well, who could have predicted these?

1021
01:05:30,280 --> 01:05:32,560
Look, I don't want
you and Chloe to worry.

1022
01:05:32,600 --> 01:05:35,480
- You'll always have a safety net.
- You're too generous, sir.

1023
01:05:35,560 --> 01:05:37,080
Oh, no, you've made Chloe happy,

1024
01:05:37,160 --> 01:05:39,200
and that means a great deal
to Eleanor and me.

1025
01:06:40,400 --> 01:06:44,360
Well, I think it's gonna be
an amazing holiday. Don't you, Chris?

1026
01:06:44,440 --> 01:06:45,800
Yes.

1027
01:06:45,840 --> 01:06:49,560
We have a choice of sleeping
on the boat or in the different hotels.

1028
01:06:49,640 --> 01:06:50,600
- Boat.
- Boat.

1029
01:06:50,680 --> 01:06:51,880
- Every time.
- Good. I say the boat.

1030
01:06:51,960 --> 01:06:53,320
Do you know he's never been
to the Greek Islands.

1031
01:06:53,400 --> 01:06:54,640
- What?
- No.

1032
01:06:54,720 --> 01:06:56,240
- No, he's never been.
- You'll love it.

1033
01:06:56,320 --> 01:06:59,160
No. I have been to Athens,
but I hear the Islands are paradise.

1034
01:06:59,240 --> 01:07:00,240
Oh, that reminds me,

1035
01:07:00,320 --> 01:07:02,760
we have to go to Sardinia to
pop in on Brook and Dougie Winston.

1036
01:07:02,840 --> 01:07:03,840
- Oh, good.
- Oh, God.

1037
01:07:03,920 --> 01:07:06,440
- No, no, the house is beautiful.
- Brook's fine, Dougie's a nightmare.

1038
01:07:06,520 --> 01:07:08,360
Sounds so romantic, doesn't it?
Mikonos and Crete.

1039
01:07:08,400 --> 01:07:09,400
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1040
01:07:09,480 --> 01:07:12,000
I'm so anxious to see all the
beautiful old temples and theaters.

1041
01:07:12,080 --> 01:07:13,080
Oh, God.

1042
01:07:13,160 --> 01:07:14,600
Yeah. Oh, I'll do that with you.
Tom can stay...

1043
01:07:14,640 --> 01:07:17,640
You know, I bought Chris
an ancient Greek fertility charm.

1044
01:07:17,680 --> 01:07:19,560
- Do you remember?
- I'll never forget.

1045
01:07:19,640 --> 01:07:21,320
I sent off for that fertility thingy.

1046
01:07:21,400 --> 01:07:24,320
He had to put it under
his pillow for two months.

1047
01:07:24,400 --> 01:07:27,400
And absolutely nothing happened,
of course.

1048
01:07:27,480 --> 01:07:28,440
Poor thing.

1049
01:07:28,520 --> 01:07:31,120
- I'd just subjected him to the torture.
- They think he's firing blanks.

1050
01:07:31,200 --> 01:07:32,200
- Oh, shut up!
- Hello?

1051
01:07:32,280 --> 01:07:33,960
I miss you.

1052
01:07:34,520 --> 01:07:36,760
- Love me. Just love me.
- No, because it's not funny.

1053
01:07:36,840 --> 01:07:38,320
- It's not funny.
- I'm sorry.

1054
01:07:38,360 --> 01:07:40,520
Proof is in the pudding,
and there ain't been any pudding.

1055
01:07:40,600 --> 01:07:42,680
- I can't get away right now.
- Well, you have to.

1056
01:07:42,760 --> 01:07:44,360
When can you get here?

1057
01:07:45,560 --> 01:07:47,800
Tomorrow. No, Monday.

1058
01:07:47,840 --> 01:07:49,200
Look...

1059
01:07:49,880 --> 01:07:51,600
It's a three-day weekend.

1060
01:07:51,880 --> 01:07:53,440
Tuesday.

1061
01:07:54,000 --> 01:07:56,000
Chris, I need to see you.

1062
01:07:57,160 --> 01:07:59,840
I'll see what I can do.
I'll call you right back.

1063
01:07:59,920 --> 01:08:02,360
I would love to meet Barbra Streisand.

1064
01:08:02,440 --> 01:08:05,400
She's meant to be really lovely.
She's with that other American fella.

1065
01:08:05,480 --> 01:08:07,040
- Who was that?
- Oh, I'm such an idiot.

1066
01:08:07,120 --> 01:08:09,520
I forgot to sign some papers.
I may have to drive into town.

1067
01:08:09,560 --> 01:08:10,560
Jack Garner?

1068
01:08:10,640 --> 01:08:12,680
You can't go,
it's a bank holiday weekend.

1069
01:08:12,760 --> 01:08:14,040
The traffic'll be terrible.

1070
01:08:14,120 --> 01:08:16,520
- James Garner, that's it.
- I mean, we've all got plans.

1071
01:08:16,600 --> 01:08:17,560
I don't mean today.

1072
01:08:17,640 --> 01:08:19,320
They named their little dog
after Elaine Paige.

1073
01:08:19,400 --> 01:08:20,720
Well, surely it can wait
a couple of days.

1074
01:08:20,800 --> 01:08:22,600
- Why did they do that?
- 'Cause it howls all night long.

1075
01:08:22,680 --> 01:08:24,200
- Yes, I'm sure it can.
- Oh, that's mean.

1076
01:08:24,280 --> 01:08:26,040
I know. And it's
terribly small and furry.

1077
01:08:26,120 --> 01:08:27,120
That's mean.

1078
01:08:27,680 --> 01:08:30,200
I think tomorrow
we should go for a morning ride.

1079
01:08:30,280 --> 01:08:31,760
I've some lovely new horses.

1080
01:08:31,840 --> 01:08:33,440
Do you remember when
Chris came here first,

1081
01:08:33,480 --> 01:08:35,480
and he had some
serious qualms about riding?

1082
01:08:35,520 --> 01:08:36,640
- I spoke to Teddy.
- How is he?

1083
01:08:36,720 --> 01:08:38,520
Well, this morning he was talking
about buying a horse of his own.

1084
01:08:38,600 --> 01:08:40,200
- No.
- Yeah.

1085
01:08:40,280 --> 01:08:41,800
I don't know, it was all in good fun.

1086
01:08:41,880 --> 01:08:43,000
- Where from?
- Anyway...

1087
01:08:43,080 --> 01:08:45,480
- I think Nan's got a really nice mare.
...he's a wonderful new horse.

1088
01:08:45,560 --> 01:08:48,360
Telephone call, sir.
She said it was important.

1089
01:08:51,440 --> 01:08:52,960
Excuse me.

1090
01:08:54,280 --> 01:08:56,280
- Tomorrow morning?
- Do you wanna come?

1091
01:08:56,360 --> 01:08:59,040
That bloody phone
has not stopped ringing all weekend.

1092
01:08:59,120 --> 01:09:01,160
- I know.
- It's so irritating.

1093
01:09:01,600 --> 01:09:02,600
Hello?

1094
01:09:02,680 --> 01:09:04,840
I tried to call your mobile,
but it's off.

1095
01:09:05,320 --> 01:09:07,280
Are you mad calling me here?

1096
01:09:07,880 --> 01:09:09,520
When are you coming over?

1097
01:09:09,600 --> 01:09:11,600
I'm trying to make it for tomorrow.

1098
01:09:11,680 --> 01:09:13,760
I can't wait till tomorrow,
I'm going crazy.

1099
01:09:13,840 --> 01:09:16,680
- What the hell's the matter?
- I'm pregnant.

1100
01:09:22,840 --> 01:09:24,840
I'll talk to you tomorrow.

1101
01:09:24,920 --> 01:09:27,400
'Cause we've got to go
and try and look at this...

1102
01:09:27,440 --> 01:09:30,560
...horse for Chris.
- They got it in the navy?

1103
01:09:31,320 --> 01:09:34,240
Yeah, the... It was lack of enough
vegetables, or something.

1104
01:09:34,320 --> 01:09:36,840
I wonder if that's why they took
lemons and oranges...

1105
01:09:36,920 --> 01:09:38,240
Well, they only had biscuits.

1106
01:09:38,320 --> 01:09:40,680
Well, that's where
Rose's Lime Cordial originated...

1107
01:09:40,760 --> 01:09:44,520
- Who keeps calling?
- It was Samantha, my secretary.

1108
01:09:44,600 --> 01:09:47,720
I'm afraid I won't be able
to go riding tomorrow. I can't help it.

1109
01:09:47,800 --> 01:09:50,080
I thought Samantha said she was
going to her parents this weekend.

1110
01:09:50,160 --> 01:09:52,400
I know, it's all my fault. Poor girl.

1111
01:09:53,320 --> 01:09:54,640
It's no big deal.

1112
01:09:54,720 --> 01:09:55,880
I'll pop back into town.

1113
01:09:56,000 --> 01:09:59,960
The whole thing'll take a few hours,
and it'll be off my mind. I promise.

1114
01:10:00,040 --> 01:10:01,720
- That's a shame.
- It's really sad.

1115
01:10:01,800 --> 01:10:03,400
Well, it is a pity because I...

1116
01:10:03,480 --> 01:10:05,680
I think it's unfair
on Samantha too, frankly.

1117
01:10:05,760 --> 01:10:07,120
Yeah. Well, it's unfortunate,

1118
01:10:07,200 --> 01:10:09,320
but, you know,
Chris has a lot of responsibility.

1119
01:10:09,400 --> 01:10:11,040
Well, anyway,
let's not worry about it. Let's...

1120
01:10:11,120 --> 01:10:12,600
- Slave driver.
- Look, as long as we make lamb bone.

1121
01:10:12,680 --> 01:10:13,680
- Can you, can you?
- Well, I think so.

1122
01:10:13,760 --> 01:10:13,840
- How the hell did you get pregnant?
- I told you that weekend last month

1123
01:10:13,840 --> 01:10:16,520
- How the hell did you get pregnant?
- I told you that weekend last month

1124
01:10:16,600 --> 01:10:18,400
that we needed to be careful
and I didn't have protection,

1125
01:10:18,480 --> 01:10:20,040
but you couldn't wait.

1126
01:10:21,960 --> 01:10:23,840
What unbelievable bad luck.

1127
01:10:23,920 --> 01:10:26,720
Christ, I can't get my wife pregnant
no matter how hard I try,

1128
01:10:26,760 --> 01:10:28,600
and the minute you're unprotected
I knock you up.

1129
01:10:28,680 --> 01:10:30,480
It's 'cause you love me,
and you don't love her.

1130
01:10:30,560 --> 01:10:31,560
Is that your interpretation?

1131
01:10:31,640 --> 01:10:33,720
It's a child conceived
out of genuine passion,

1132
01:10:33,800 --> 01:10:36,360
not as part of some fertility project.

1133
01:10:36,440 --> 01:10:38,360
OK. Well I'll go with you,
and we'll get it sorted.

1134
01:10:38,440 --> 01:10:40,200
- I'm not doing that again.
- Again?

1135
01:10:40,240 --> 01:10:42,800
- What's that supposed to mean?
- It's the third time.

1136
01:10:42,880 --> 01:10:45,400
I did it once when I was younger,
and then I did it for Tom.

1137
01:10:45,480 --> 01:10:47,280
I didn't want to, but he insisted.

1138
01:10:47,360 --> 01:10:49,320
Nola, I really can't see any other way.

1139
01:10:49,400 --> 01:10:51,400
- Why can't I just have it?
- And what?

1140
01:10:51,480 --> 01:10:54,400
- And we'll raise it together.
- That's obviously not possible.

1141
01:10:54,480 --> 01:10:56,440
Why? You hate yourjob,
you hate your life.

1142
01:10:56,520 --> 01:10:59,200
I mean, it seems like a blessing.
It's a sign.

1143
01:10:59,280 --> 01:11:00,960
Look, Nola, I have to go.

1144
01:11:01,040 --> 01:11:03,000
I'm juggling six things
at the same time

1145
01:11:03,080 --> 01:11:05,640
just to make
this trip to the city look legit.

1146
01:11:07,240 --> 01:11:08,600
I'll talk to you on Tuesday.

1147
01:11:08,680 --> 01:11:09,920
Chris...

1148
01:11:10,000 --> 01:11:13,120
You must... I expect you
to do the right thing, OK?

1149
01:11:13,200 --> 01:11:15,720
I'm not walking away from this.

1150
01:11:17,360 --> 01:11:20,320
Is anything the matter?
You seemed very gloomy all weekend.

1151
01:11:22,640 --> 01:11:25,760
- I wanted to talk to you.
- What about?

1152
01:11:26,760 --> 01:11:28,880
Us.

1153
01:11:29,360 --> 01:11:31,320
Is something wrong?

1154
01:11:33,240 --> 01:11:35,560
Yeah. There is.

1155
01:11:37,040 --> 01:11:38,040
What?

1156
01:11:38,120 --> 01:11:41,160
If you're still taking a hammering
financially in the market,

1157
01:11:41,240 --> 01:11:42,720
you know it's not a problem.

1158
01:11:43,240 --> 01:11:45,920
I can't keep leaning
on your father, Chloe.

1159
01:11:47,040 --> 01:11:50,320
Papa gets more pleasure
out of helping his family,

1160
01:11:50,400 --> 01:11:53,920
than all the possessions he owns.
You know that.

1161
01:11:56,920 --> 01:11:58,680
What is it?

1162
01:12:03,200 --> 01:12:06,560
Is it something to do
with those phone calls you kept getting?

1163
01:12:07,680 --> 01:12:10,920
Because you acted
really strangely after each of them.

1164
01:12:15,280 --> 01:12:17,680
Are you having an affair?

1165
01:12:18,640 --> 01:12:20,880
Am I having an affair?

1166
01:12:20,960 --> 01:12:23,040
Yeah, that's what I asked.

1167
01:12:25,080 --> 01:12:27,440
- No.
- You are.

1168
01:12:27,480 --> 01:12:29,680
Of course I'm not. Don't be silly.

1169
01:12:40,480 --> 01:12:43,000
Do you not love me anymore?

1170
01:12:45,200 --> 01:12:47,400
Of course I love you.

1171
01:12:48,640 --> 01:12:50,800
Well, what's wrong?

1172
01:12:54,000 --> 01:12:56,240
I just feel like I'm letting you down.

1173
01:12:56,280 --> 01:12:58,320
You're not. How?

1174
01:13:01,320 --> 01:13:03,960
Is it because I'm not getting pregnant?

1175
01:13:07,280 --> 01:13:09,280
I just...

1176
01:13:09,920 --> 01:13:12,320
...feel so guilty.

1177
01:13:13,120 --> 01:13:15,840
So terribly guilty.

1178
01:13:15,920 --> 01:13:18,240
Listen, Chris.

1179
01:13:18,320 --> 01:13:21,760
We've both been to the doctor.
We're both perfectly healthy.

1180
01:13:21,840 --> 01:13:26,280
I can conceive and you're perfectly
capable of making a woman pregnant.

1181
01:13:27,960 --> 01:13:32,240
Is it me? Have I been horribly pushy
and obnoxious on the subject?

1182
01:13:33,120 --> 01:13:37,960
Look, I... I just want a baby.
I want to have our baby.

1183
01:13:39,920 --> 01:13:42,640
We haven't been lucky yet, that's all.

1184
01:13:46,240 --> 01:13:47,800
Oh, Chloe.

1185
01:13:53,760 --> 01:13:56,000
Let's get off the subject.

1186
01:13:56,040 --> 01:14:00,040
Having a child should be something
that makes us both happy and excited,

1187
01:14:00,120 --> 01:14:03,880
not a cause of all this
tension and anxiety and...

1188
01:14:07,520 --> 01:14:09,520
I had to talk to somebody.

1189
01:14:10,800 --> 01:14:12,160
I'm really suffering.

1190
01:14:12,240 --> 01:14:15,320
Whatever you tell me goes no further.

1191
01:14:16,560 --> 01:14:19,560
I'm contemplating leaving my wife
for another woman.

1192
01:14:20,960 --> 01:14:22,920
But when the time came to tell her...

1193
01:14:23,960 --> 01:14:25,560
...I couldn't do it.

1194
01:14:25,640 --> 01:14:28,120
Yeah, well, it's not the easiest
thing in the world to do, is it?

1195
01:14:30,280 --> 01:14:31,960
It's crazy.

1196
01:14:33,240 --> 01:14:35,960
I can see no real future
with this other woman.

1197
01:14:36,120 --> 01:14:38,400
And I have a very
comfortable life with my wife.

1198
01:14:38,480 --> 01:14:41,800
- Yeah, but if you don't love her...
- I'm not saying I don't love her.

1199
01:14:41,880 --> 01:14:44,480
Just not in the way I feel
about this other woman.

1200
01:14:44,520 --> 01:14:46,240
Right.

1201
01:14:46,960 --> 01:14:50,120
Maybe it's finally the difference
between love and lust.

1202
01:14:50,240 --> 01:14:52,720
But what the hell
am I going to do if I leave Chloe?

1203
01:14:55,000 --> 01:14:58,640
I don't fool myself that I haven't
gotten used to a certain kind of living.

1204
01:14:58,720 --> 01:15:02,120
Am I supposed to give it all up?
For what?

1205
01:15:02,800 --> 01:15:04,360
Is it for a woman you love?

